From gschweik at staffmail.ed.ac.uk  Tue Apr  9 14:56:20 2013
From: gschweik at staffmail.ed.ac.uk (Gabriele Schweikert)
Date: Tue, 09 Apr 2013 13:56:20 +0100
Subject: [Bioc-devel] MMDiff: new package for differential ChIP-Seq peaks
Message-ID: <20130409135620.31174yth7oaff8kk@www.staffmail.ed.ac.uk>

Hi,

this is just to briefly inform you that a new package called MMDiff is  
now available.
It's a statistical testing method specifically designed to compare  
ChIP-Seq data sets. It takes advantage of higher order features to  
detect shape changes in ChIP-Seq peaks and should also be applicable  
to other -Seq methods, like DNase-Seq. Biological replicates are used  
to estimate biological variance. Any comments highly appreciated.


Many thanks,

Gabriele Schweikert




